#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:13
msgid "WMS server with GeoServer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:15
msgid ""
"Now that we have a pl/pgsql wrapper, we will make it available as a WMS "
"layer using `GeoServer <http://geoserver.org/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:18
msgid ""
"The installation of GeoServer is out of scope of this workshop but if you're"
" using the `OSGeo LiveDVD <http://live.osgeo.org>`_ the server is already "
"installed and only needs to be started."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:23
msgid "Connect to the administration page"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:25
msgid ""
"In order to create the WMS layer, we need to connect to the administration "
"page of GeoServer. On the OSGeo LiveDVD, open the *Applications* menu on the"
" desktop and then *Geoservers* > *GeoServer* > *Start GeoServer*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:30
msgid ""
"Once the server is up, the `administration page "
"<http://localhost:8082/geoserver/web>`_ should open, click the *Login* "
"button and entrer the admin credentials:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:34
msgid "Username: ``admin``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:35
msgid "Password: ``geoserver``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:38
msgid "Create the layer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:40
msgid ""
"Now that we are logged in as an administrator we can start create our layer."
" In GeoServer terminology we will create an SQL View (see the `official "
"documentation "
"<http://docs.geoserver.org/latest/en/user/data/database/sqlview.html>`_ for "
"more info)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:47
msgid ""
"The first thing to do is to create a new **Workspace** for pgrouting: in the"
" left menu of the page, inside the *Data* section, click *Workspaces* and "
"then *Add new workspace*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:51 ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:62
msgid "Fill the form with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:53
msgid "Name: ``pgrouting``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:54
msgid "Namespace URI: ``http://pgrouting.org/``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:56
msgid "Add press the submit button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:58
msgid ""
"Next step: create a new **Store** linked to the workspace. Still in the left"
" menu, click *Stores* and then *Add new Store*. Here we can choose the type "
"of data source to configure. Choose *PostGIS*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:64
msgid "Basic Store Info:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:66
msgid "Workspace (select): ``pgrouting``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:67
msgid "Data Source Name: ``pgrouting``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:69
msgid "Connection Parameters:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:71
msgid "host: ``localhost``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:72
msgid "port: ``5432``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:73
msgid "database: ``pgrouting-workshop``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:74
msgid "schema: ``public``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:75
msgid "user: ``postgres``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:76
msgid "password: blank"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:78
msgid "The rest of the values can be left untouched."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:80
msgid ""
"Finally, our next task is to create the **Layer**. Click the *Layers* menu "
"and then *Add a new resource*. Select the newly created workspace and store "
"pair: ``pgrouting:pgrouting``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:84
msgid "Inside the text, click *Configure new SQL view*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:86
msgid "Name the view ``pgrouting`` and fill the *SQL statement* with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:94
msgid ""
"In the *SQL view parameters*, click *Guess parameters from SQL*; the list "
"displayed represents the parameters from the SQL above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:97
msgid "For each parameter:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:99
msgid "Set the default value to: `0`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:100
msgid "Change the validation regular expression to ``^-?[\\d.]+$``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:102
msgid "The regular expression will only match numbers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:104
msgid "In the *Attributes* list:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:106
msgid "Hit *Refresh*, one attribute should appear (called *st_makeline*)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:107
msgid ""
"Change the type to ``LineString`` and the SRID of the geometry column from "
"``-1`` to ``4326``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:109
msgid "Save the form."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:111
msgid "Finally, we need to setup the rest of the layer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:113
msgid ""
"The only thing to do in this screen is to make sure that the coordinate "
"reference system is correct: the geometries in the database are in "
"`EPSG:4326` but we want to display them in `EPSG:3857` because the "
"OPenLayers map where the layer will be dispayed is in this projection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:119
msgid ""
"Scoll down to the *coordinate reference system* section  and change the "
"**Declared SRS** to ``EPSG:3857`` and the **SRS handling** to ``Reproject "
"native to declared``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/geoserver.rst:123
msgid ""
"Click the *Compute from data* and *Compute from native bounds* link to "
"automatically set the layer bounds. Click the *Save* at the bottom of the "
"page to create the layer."
msgstr ""
